# Commit Template for ARES ChronoFabric Project
#
# Please follow this format for consistent commit messages:
#
# <type>: <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore, perf, build
#
# Guidelines:
# - Use imperative mood in subject line
# - Keep subject line under 50 characters
# - Separate subject from body with blank line  
# - Wrap body at 72 characters
# - Focus on what and why, not how
#
# Examples:
# feat: Add quantum temporal correlation engine
# fix: Resolve circular dependency between core and time modules
# docs: Update API documentation for phase packet system
#
# Do not include:
# - References to AI assistance
# - External authorship attributions
# - Automated generation notices
#
# All commits are authored by: Ididia Serfaty